Statically Typed Lanaguage (C)   -> Static
Loosely Typed Lanaguage (JS)     -> Dynamic


Basic/ Primitive Data Types (Scala Type)
    -> Character (-)    
    -> Number   -> Integer  -> Signed Int & Unsigned Int  -> Float  -> Double  -> Long
    -> Boolean 
    -> String 

Other Data Types 
    -> undefined
    -> null
    -> NaN


Compound Data Type
    -> array

Structured Data Type
    -> Object



JS can handle Type Juggling !
    -> automatically convert data type according to the input


JS can also handle Type Coercion ! 
    -> automatically adjust the data types when comparing two vars



Escape character in String
    -> let time = '3 O\' Clock'


Template String
    -> let name = "Bob"
       let greet = `Hello ${name}`          // Hello Bob


Undefined, null, NaN
    -> let num1             // undefined
       let num2 = 1         // Number
       let num3 = null      // null
       num1 + num2          // NaN


Falsy Values
    -> 0
    -> ""  empty String
    -> null
    -> undefined
    -> NaN

PS: others are all Truthy Value

